comment._content: Two A-3B Skywarrior VAH-123 Replacement Training squadron Tail code NJ. Nearest is Bu No 138955 Modex 317 Modex 320 serial number unknown. Date unknown A3D-2 Skywarrior 138955 Modex 508 code AC of CVG-3, pictured after a carrier landing mishap: commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:A3D-2_nose_wheel_collapse... Douglas A3D-2 Skywarrior BuNo 138955 VAH-9 Hoot Owls after nose wheel collapsed during recovery on USS Saratoga (CVA-60), 1959-1960. Notes on KA-3B 138955 Built as A3D-2 Number 99 on Skywarrior production line. Accepted by US Navy April 1957. Became A-3B from 1962 Converted to KA-3B by NARF Alameda June 1967. Salvaged at NARF Alameda April 1970 after inflight accident. As yet there is no known web based record of the rest of the existence of 138955 or circumstances of the ‘inflight accident’.
